Key Match Events: Trae Young made a 49-foot game-winning shot with time expiring, giving the Atlanta Hawks a three-point win
Post-Match Reflections: Collin Sexton felt that Trae Young made a tough shot, but also acknowledged that he couldn't have pressured him up any more
Sexton praised Young's ability to make shots like that saying 'those two guys, for sure are gonna make it'
Miscellaneous Highlights: The game was a tough one for Utah Jazz fans as they lost to the Atlanta Hawks 124-121
The loss takes the Jazz to their 26th of the 2024-25 campaign, ending their hopes of obtaining their first three-game win streak of the season
Others: Collin Sexton had 24 points, four rebounds, and three assists in the game, including a game-tying three in the final seconds
Trae Young ended the game with 24 points, 20 assists, and the game-winner
